[u][b]Section 3 - Extra[/b][/u]
[b]3.1 - Frequently Asked Questions[/b]
[b]Question:[/b] What's a good free file host for my cache.zip?
[b]Answer:[/b] You can use any host that allows direct linking. I personally use this site:
[url=http://www.fileden.com/]http://www.fileden.com/[/url]

[b]Question:[/b] Ric, it's too hard. Can you make it for me?
[b]Answer:[/b] No, I don't do this for people anymore. You gotta learn how to make a webclient for when you update your client.

[b]Question:[/b] I get a blank page with a red X on it. What do I do?
[b]Answer:[/b] Right click and press Java Console and read the error.

[b]Question:[/b] The java console says it cannot find client.class, What should I do?
[b]Answer:[/b] I recommend deleting all the class files and recompile your client.

[b]Question:[/b] I get the 1,2,3,4,5 error. What do I do?
[b]Answer:[/b] Something is missing, corrupted or done wrong.

[b]Question:[/b] I get a java heap space error, What do I do?
[b]Answer:[/b] Make sure you have <param name="java_arguments" value="-Xmx1024m"> in your applet code.
